name: TWINSUK_AC
detail: Alternative allele count in called genotypes in UK10K TWINSUK cohort.

name: TWINSUK_AF
detail: Alternative allele frequency in called genotypes in UK10K TWINSUK cohort.

name: TWINSUK_AN
detail: Total allele count in called genotypes in UK10K TWINSUK cohort.

name: TargetScan_context++_score_percentile
detail: context++ score is a measure of favorableness of the\nsite for the miRNA family. The higer the percentile, the more favorable (from TargetScan)

name: UTR3_miRNA_target
detail: the gene-miRNA pair, if the site is located within a predicted (conserved)\ntarget of conserved miRNA families(from TargetScan)

name: Uniprot_acc
detail: Uniprot accession number matching the Ensembl_proteinid\nMultiple entries separated by ";".

name: Uniprot_entry
detail: Uniprot entry ID matching the Ensembl_proteinid\nMultiple entries separated by ";".

name: aaalt
detail: alternative amino acid\n"." if the variant is a splicing site SNP (2bp on each end of an intron)

name: aapos
detail: amino acid position as to the protein.\n"-1" if the variant is a splicing site SNP (2bp on each end of an intron). Multiple entries separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_proteinid\nMultiple entries separated by ";", corresponding to Ensembl_proteinid

name: aaref
detail: reference amino acid\n"." if the variant is a splicing site SNP (2bp on each end of an intron)

name: cds_strand
detail: coding sequence (CDS) strand (+ or -)

name: codon_degeneracy
detail: degenerate type (0, 2 or 3)

name: codonpos
detail: position on the codon (1, 2 or 3)

name: fathmm-MKL_coding_group
detail: fathmm-MKL coding group, the feature group used for the coding prediction.

name: fathmm-MKL_coding_pred
detail: If a fathmm-MKL_coding_score is >0.5 the corresponding nsSNV\nis predicted as "D(AMAGING)"; otherwise it is predicted as "N(EUTRAL)".

name: fathmm-MKL_coding_rankscore
detail: the rank of the fathmm-MKL_coding_score among all fathmm-MKL_coding_scores in genome

name: fathmm-MKL_coding_score
detail: fathmm-MKL coding prediction probability, the larger the number the more likely damaging\nthe threshold separating deleterious prediction and neutral prediction is 0.5.

name: fathmm-MKL_non-coding_group
detail: fathmm-MKL non-coding group, the feature group used for the non-coding prediction

name: fathmm-MKL_non-coding_pred
detail: If a fathmm-MKL_non-coding_score is >0.5 the corresponding nsSNV\nis predicted as "D(AMAGING)"; otherwise it is predicted as "N(EUTRAL)".

name: fathmm-MKL_non-coding_rankscore
detail: the rank of the fathmm-MKL_non-coding_score among all fathmm-MKL_non-coding_scores in genome

name: fathmm-MKL_non-coding_score
detail: fathmm-MKL non-coding prediction probability, the larger the number the more likely damaging;\nthe threshold separating deleterious prediction and neutral prediction is 0.5.

name: fathmm-XF_coding_or_noncoding
detail: whether the prediction is based on the model for coding region\nor noncoding region

name: fathmm-XF_pred
detail: If a fathmm-XF_score is >0.5 the corresponding nsSNV\nis predicted as "D(AMAGING)"; otherwise it is predicted as "N(EUTRAL)".

name: fathmm-XF_rankscore
detail: the rank of the fathmm-XF_score among all fathmm-XF_scores in genome

name: fathmm-XF_score
detail: fathmm-XF prediction probability, the larger the number the more likely damaging;\nthe threshold separating deleterious prediction and neutral prediction is 0.5.

name: funseq_noncoding_score
detail: funseq-like noncoding score range 0-6, each of the previous 5 columns\ncontribute 1 if "YES", or 0 if "NO"; the column Motif_breaking contribute 1 if it is not a "."\nnot a "."

name: genename
detail: gene name; if the nsSNV can be assigned to multiple genes, gene names are\nseparated by ";"

name: network_hub
detail: whether the target gene is a network hub based on funseq-0.1

name: refcodon
detail: reference codon

name: sensitive
detail: whether defined as sensitive region based on funseq-0.1

name: sno_miRNA_name
detail: the name of snoRNA or miRNA if the site is located within (from miRBase/snoRNABase)

name: sno_miRNA_type
detail: the type of snoRNA or miRNA (from miRBase/snoRNABase)

name: splicing_consensus_ada_score
detail: splicing-change prediction for splicing consensus SNPs\nbased on adaboost. If the score >0.6, it predicts that the splicing will be changed, otherwise it predicts the splicing will not be changed.\notherwise it predicts the splicing will not be changed.

name: splicing_consensus_rf_score
detail: splicing-change prediction for splicing consensus SNPs\nbased on random forest. If the score >0.6, it predicts that the splicing will be changed, otherwise it predicts the splicing will not be changed\notherwise it predicts the splicing will not be changed

name: target_gene
detail: target gene (for promoter, enhancer, etc.) based on funseq-0.1

name: ultra_sensitive
detail: whether defined as ultra-sensitive region based funseq-0.1
